  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6595.28 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-10.3B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+14.4B), dealers are in full amplification mode and likely buying this dip aggressively as spot approaches the 6590 buy zone. The recent regime flip into BREAKOUT with -5.6B total GEX means any sustained move through these critical levels will force violent hedging flows - break below 6590 triggers more dealer buying while a push above 6605 forces dealer selling. Watch 6580 (-9.7B) as the next major amplification level if we break the 6590 support, while 6605-6610 represents the key resistance band where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile swings between 6590-6605 with dealers amplifying any breakout moves.",
